        <h2 class="mb-3">1. What is it?</h2>

        <p>
            <!-- Your full paragraph here -->
            The groundwork for BCIs and modern brain research was made by the invention of electroencephalography (EEG) in 1924 by Hans Berger. His research and development of EEG allows us to read and measure electrical activity of the brain (Awuah Wireko et al., 2024). After Berger’s discovery, in 1973 Jacques Vidal coined the term Brain-Computer Interface and in 1977 in one of his experiments he was able to control a “cursor-like graphical object on a computer screen” with the use of EEG (Vijayendra et al., 2018). These two people provide the main groundwork for BCIs
        </p>

